The paper presents a framework for self-localization of parking robots using LiDAR and odometry as sensors. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of square-like landmarks and image processing techniques to deduce the global pose of the robot suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) may also be relevant sub-categories. The use of Particle Filter for real-time localization suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) may also be relevant. Finally, the use of odometry as a secondary information source suggests that control systems (cs.SY) may also be relevant.
